WEBVTT

00:01.796 --> 00:05.386
<i>POP: Warden Lacy had locked</i>
<i>the devil in a box</i>

00:05.386 --> 00:09.435
<i>to put an end to all</i>
<i>the horrors we've seen.</i>

00:09.435 --> 00:13.778
<i>The stain,</i>
<i>the curse on our town.</i>

00:13.778 --> 00:15.907
<i>That's what God told me.</i>

00:15.907 --> 00:17.285
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:17.285 --> 00:18.705
<i>ANNIE: I'm just</i>
<i>passing through.</i>

00:18.705 --> 00:20.667
Your ad said you needed
temp RNs.

00:20.667 --> 00:22.503
<i>JAMAL: You on any medications?</i>
<i>ANNIE: No.</i>

00:22.503 --> 00:26.595
<i>JOY: What's happening?</i>
<i>ANNIE: We're getting out.</i>

00:26.595 --> 00:29.392
<i>Just hang on to me.</i>
<i>[whimpers] Don't make a sound.</i>

00:29.392 --> 00:32.064
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:32.064 --> 00:33.610
Joy?

00:33.610 --> 00:35.947
‐ Although he had no children
of his own,

00:35.947 --> 00:38.410
Pop raised Chris and John.

00:38.410 --> 00:40.164
Everything you fucking have
I gave you.

00:40.164 --> 00:42.293
‐ You gave me shit.
I took what I deserve.

00:42.293 --> 00:44.130
Remember, Sergeant Major?

00:44.130 --> 00:47.971
‐ You'd be wise not
to bring that up again.

00:47.971 --> 00:50.225
<i>ABDI: You told Nadia?</i>

00:50.225 --> 00:51.729
‐ Nadia!
[gunshots]

00:51.729 --> 00:53.482
<i>POP: She figured it out</i>
<i>on her own.</i>

00:53.482 --> 00:55.612
<i>ABDI: Well, now she won't talk</i>
<i>to me either.</i>

00:55.612 --> 00:58.116
<i>Is there anything</i>
<i>you can't fuck up?</i>

00:58.116 --> 01:05.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:43.833 --> 01:45.837
[no audio]

01:45.837 --> 01:51.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:54.228 --> 01:57.234
<i>[man speaking indistinctly</i>
<i>on radio]</i>

01:58.863 --> 02:01.869
[clattering]

02:06.419 --> 02:09.843
[cane smacking]

02:28.421 --> 02:31.427
[clock ticking]

02:35.895 --> 02:39.277
[floorboards creaking]

02:39.277 --> 02:41.489
[thud, blood splatters]

02:41.489 --> 02:44.495
<i>[Johnny Cash' "Danny Boy"]</i>

02:44.495 --> 02:51.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:51.467 --> 02:54.473
[distant car alarms wailing,
horns honking]

02:56.896 --> 03:00.027
JOHNNY CASH:
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

03:00.027 --> 03:04.995
♪ The pipes,
the pipes are calling ♪

03:04.995 --> 03:09.003
♪ From glen to glen ♪

03:09.003 --> 03:11.717
♪ And down the mountainside ♪

03:11.717 --> 03:14.598
[car engine revving]

03:14.598 --> 03:17.311
♪ The summer's gone ♪

03:17.311 --> 03:21.361
♪ And all the roses fallen ♪

03:21.361 --> 03:23.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:23.031 --> 03:25.703
♪ It's you, it's you ♪

03:25.703 --> 03:29.795
♪ Must go and I must bide ♪

03:29.795 --> 03:31.381
‐ She's awake.

03:31.381 --> 03:35.723
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:35.723 --> 03:37.602
AUGUSTIN:
Are you feeling better?

03:37.602 --> 03:39.063
‐ Much.

03:39.063 --> 03:40.817
‐ Your vessel was blind, yes?

03:40.817 --> 03:42.319
‐ So I gather.

03:42.319 --> 03:44.240
AUGUSTIN:
Well, then...

03:44.240 --> 03:47.454
to whatever part
of her is left,

03:47.454 --> 03:48.540
a gift.

03:48.540 --> 03:50.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:50.085 --> 03:51.797
Now I need something
in return.

03:51.797 --> 03:54.803
JOHNNY CASH:
♪ I'll be here ♪

03:54.803 --> 03:56.598
♪ In sunshine ♪

03:56.598 --> 03:57.934
[tires screeching]

03:57.934 --> 04:01.441
♪ Or in shadow ♪
[woman screaming]

04:01.441 --> 04:04.573
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

04:04.573 --> 04:10.459
♪ Oh, Danny boy,
I love you so ♪

04:10.459 --> 04:13.006
‐ I need a memory of hers.

04:13.006 --> 04:15.553
Your husband kept
a man in a cage‐‐

04:15.553 --> 04:18.851
a secret cage beneath
the prison.

04:18.851 --> 04:21.732
JOHNNY CASH:
♪ You'll come and find ♪

04:21.732 --> 04:27.786
♪ The place where I am lying ♪

04:27.786 --> 04:30.708
AUGUSTIN: But I don't think
it was just a man.

04:30.708 --> 04:32.629
I think it was an angel.

04:32.629 --> 04:34.465
‐ Our angel?

04:34.465 --> 04:36.595
‐ [crying]
[gun clatters]

04:36.595 --> 04:40.310
Oh, Papa!

04:40.310 --> 04:42.690
‐ No, no, no, no!

04:43.984 --> 04:48.201
‐ I need to know if it was him
and where our angel is now.

04:48.201 --> 04:52.919
‐ I only know that
the warden recorded in detail

04:52.919 --> 04:55.507
every struggle in letters

04:55.507 --> 04:59.515
which he sent to his friend,
Sheriff Pangborn.

04:59.515 --> 05:02.981
‐ And these letters,
where are they now?

05:02.981 --> 05:05.277
‐ In possession
of the collector,

05:05.277 --> 05:08.951
the one who takes
cast‐off things.

05:08.951 --> 05:10.580
‐ Pop Merrill?

05:10.580 --> 05:12.207
‐ Yes.

05:12.207 --> 05:15.631
JOHNNY CASH:
♪ And I will rest in peace ♪

05:15.631 --> 05:19.513
♪ Until you come ♪

05:19.513 --> 05:24.608
♪ To me ♪

05:24.608 --> 05:30.578
♪ ♪

05:32.665 --> 05:35.796
‐ [breathing heavily]

05:35.796 --> 05:38.509
Where's Abdi?

05:38.509 --> 05:40.848
‐ [whispering]
Abdi...

05:40.848 --> 05:42.434
[motorcycle engine revving]

05:42.434 --> 05:43.771
Abdi...

05:44.981 --> 05:46.275
POP:
Nadia!

05:47.444 --> 05:49.365
Nadia!

05:49.365 --> 05:51.535
Stop!

05:51.535 --> 05:53.289
CHANCE:
No, please listen!

05:53.289 --> 05:54.793
Please, please, please,
wait, wait, wait!

05:54.793 --> 05:56.379
Wait, I'm not one of them,
okay?

05:56.379 --> 05:58.174
I saw your truck!
It's not safe!

05:58.174 --> 06:00.345
You got to get out of here!
But they're coming!

06:00.345 --> 06:01.848
They're right down the road,

06:01.848 --> 06:04.311
and they're killing everyone
who's left!

06:04.311 --> 06:05.773
‐ In the truck, now.

06:05.773 --> 06:08.612
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:08.612 --> 06:10.866
NADIA: Get in!
[truck engine turning over]

06:10.866 --> 06:12.494
Go, Pop!

06:12.494 --> 06:15.375
[tires squealing]

06:15.375 --> 06:17.462
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:17.462 --> 06:19.676
[engines revving]

06:19.676 --> 06:22.514
[tires squealing]

06:26.773 --> 06:29.236
[gunshots]

06:31.115 --> 06:33.746
[tires squealing]

06:33.746 --> 06:40.551
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:40.551 --> 06:42.262
[tires squealing, gunshot]
‐ Fuck!

06:42.262 --> 06:43.640
Shit!
CHANCE: It's them!

06:43.640 --> 06:46.437
[tires squealing, gunshots]

06:46.437 --> 06:49.986
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:49.986 --> 06:51.530
‐ Get down! Get down!

06:51.530 --> 06:53.326
‐ Stay down!

06:53.326 --> 07:00.173
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:00.173 --> 07:02.929
[gasps]
Fuck!

07:08.189 --> 07:10.861
[gunshots]

07:10.861 --> 07:13.157
[engine idling]

07:13.157 --> 07:19.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:21.800 --> 07:23.219
Move!

07:24.973 --> 07:26.601
Abdi!

07:26.601 --> 07:28.271
‐ I saw Pop's truck.
I thought maybe‐‐

07:28.271 --> 07:30.943
[speaking Somali]
‐ [gasps]

07:32.655 --> 07:33.824
‐ Come on! Come on!

07:33.824 --> 07:36.872
[bell rings]

07:38.457 --> 07:42.174
[doors clanging]

07:42.174 --> 07:44.178
ABDI: Why are they trying
to kill us?

07:44.178 --> 07:46.683
‐ Let's live long enough
to talk it out.

07:46.683 --> 07:49.689
<i>[ominous music]</i>

07:49.689 --> 07:56.703
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:16.234 --> 08:18.830
[car horn blares,
car alarms wailing]

08:23.799 --> 08:26.011
<i>POP: When Pangborn got</i>
<i>butchered by his wife,</i>

08:26.011 --> 08:28.015
I bought his trailer
and everything inside it.

08:28.015 --> 08:30.729
‐ The old sheriff?
‐ Yeah.

08:30.729 --> 08:32.942
He had these letters
from Warden Lacy.

08:32.942 --> 08:35.864
‐ And now they're both dead.
‐ Yeah.

08:35.864 --> 08:38.244
<i>Dale was kind of</i>
<i>our town historian.</i>

08:38.244 --> 08:39.706
<i>He‐‐he‐‐he always used to say</i>

08:39.706 --> 08:41.584
<i>he was in</i>
<i>the remembering business</i>

08:41.584 --> 08:43.797
<i>when everyone else's</i>
<i>stock‐in‐trade was forgetting.</i>

08:43.797 --> 08:45.843
He also said the ones that
first settled this place,

08:45.843 --> 08:48.014
the ones that died
in that first bad winter

08:48.014 --> 08:51.813
and disappeared‐‐poof‐‐
no bones even,

08:51.813 --> 08:54.861
Dale said he knew
where they went.

08:54.861 --> 08:56.698
Nowhere.

08:56.698 --> 09:00.288
He said that they never
really left.

09:01.791 --> 09:05.633
I didn't know what
he meant by that.

09:05.633 --> 09:08.429
I‐I didn't know what
he meant by that.

09:08.429 --> 09:15.443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:15.443 --> 09:18.324
<i>I didn't want to know.</i>

09:18.324 --> 09:19.827
<i>And now...</i>

09:19.827 --> 09:24.086
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:24.086 --> 09:25.589
Now I know.

09:25.589 --> 09:28.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:28.679 --> 09:30.974
[click]

09:30.974 --> 09:32.519
Goddamn generator.

09:32.519 --> 09:34.022
[electricity buzzing]

09:34.022 --> 09:35.316
<i>ABDI: Why didn't we</i>
<i>hear the sound?</i>

09:35.316 --> 09:38.615
Why aren't we hypnotized?

09:38.615 --> 09:40.118
‐ Pop?
POP: I don't know.

09:40.118 --> 09:42.707
No fucking clue.

09:42.707 --> 09:44.585
NADIA: This is insane, Pop.

09:44.585 --> 09:46.798
POP: We don't know how many of
them are roaming the streets.

09:46.798 --> 09:50.012
This is the safest place
if we keep it safe.

09:50.012 --> 09:54.271
So we need a perimeter.
‐ That's a lot of bombs.

09:54.271 --> 09:57.360
POP: I figured somebody would
be coming for me someday‐‐

09:57.360 --> 10:00.951
either the police
or something else.

10:00.951 --> 10:02.328
Take these downstairs.

10:02.328 --> 10:04.124
Put them by the doors
and the windows.

10:04.124 --> 10:06.378
Daisy‐chain them together.
Be careful.

10:06.378 --> 10:13.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:30.343 --> 10:33.265
[device beeps]

10:33.265 --> 10:38.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:38.150 --> 10:40.363
‐ [scoffs, sniffs]

10:40.363 --> 10:43.118
[sighing]

10:43.118 --> 10:50.132
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:00.444 --> 11:02.783
ABDI: Hey.

11:02.783 --> 11:04.035
Hey.

11:04.035 --> 11:11.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:35.264 --> 11:38.228
‐ Oh, shit.
Fucking wire.

11:43.530 --> 11:45.953
‐ How is any of this possible?

11:49.835 --> 11:52.298
‐ [sighs]

11:52.298 --> 11:54.344
I‐I wanted‐‐

11:54.344 --> 11:57.308
I wanted none of this for you.

11:57.308 --> 12:00.106
I brought you to a bad place.

12:00.106 --> 12:05.659
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:05.659 --> 12:06.786
[guns cocking]

12:06.786 --> 12:11.838
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:11.838 --> 12:14.844
[rattling and rumbling]

12:20.271 --> 12:23.444
[banging on door]

12:23.444 --> 12:25.949
‐ Whatever's happening here‐‐
[alarm blaring]

12:25.949 --> 12:27.619
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Door C.

12:27.619 --> 12:29.205
‐ There's someone down
in the basement.

12:29.205 --> 12:32.755
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Door C. Door C.

12:34.592 --> 12:35.886
‐ Basement.

12:35.886 --> 12:38.892
[blaring continues]

12:38.892 --> 12:41.898
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:41.898 --> 12:48.912
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:18.011 --> 13:20.015
End of the hallway.

13:59.803 --> 14:01.431
Hands up!
Up, up, up, up, up!

14:01.431 --> 14:03.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:03.352 --> 14:06.524
‐ [breathing shakily]
‐ Anne?

14:06.524 --> 14:11.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:15.627 --> 14:17.213
‐ [coughing]

14:17.213 --> 14:20.219
[breathing heavily]

14:23.266 --> 14:25.396
NADIA: The streets are teeming
with these people.

14:25.396 --> 14:28.235
There's no way you got in here
unless they wanted you to.

14:28.235 --> 14:31.032
ANNIE: Why don't you stop
wasting my time?

14:31.032 --> 14:33.871
The bad guys are out there!
They have Joy!

14:33.871 --> 14:36.585
CHANCE:
Funny thing about bad guys is
they look just like you and me.

14:36.585 --> 14:38.631
‐ I knew you were after
my daughter

14:38.631 --> 14:40.384
the minute I laid eyes on you.

14:40.384 --> 14:43.306
Why don't you ask if this one
is the real deal, huh?

14:43.306 --> 14:45.603
How about that?
JAMAL: Mr. Merrill.

14:45.603 --> 14:46.981
Anne‐‐she helped us
make it here.

14:46.981 --> 14:49.277
POP: Shut up.
You were at Marsten.

14:49.277 --> 14:51.531
‐ I already told you I was.

14:51.531 --> 14:53.201
POP:
How'd you get out?

14:54.955 --> 14:56.625
‐ I killed some people.

14:56.625 --> 14:58.546
‐ How did you get
all the way over here?

14:58.546 --> 15:00.424
‐ I killed some more people.

15:00.424 --> 15:02.261
EVELYN:
Dr. H., I don't like this.

15:02.261 --> 15:04.641
‐ Evelyn, we have to be sure.

15:04.641 --> 15:06.729
‐ They've got my daughter,

15:06.729 --> 15:09.400
and I'm‐‐I'm getting her back.

15:09.400 --> 15:10.862
That's why I'm here.

15:10.862 --> 15:13.618
So hand me a gun,
and I'll be on my way!

15:13.618 --> 15:15.496
I don't care who they are!

15:15.496 --> 15:18.628
I don't care why they're doing
whatever crazy thing it is

15:18.628 --> 15:20.130
that they're doing!

15:24.055 --> 15:26.184
‐ Let's use the Army manual.

15:26.184 --> 15:29.148
<i>[tense music]</i>

15:29.148 --> 15:30.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:30.359 --> 15:33.281
‐ Go slow.
Take your time.

15:33.281 --> 15:35.703
‐ I was at the Mellow Tiger,
and all of a sudden,

15:35.703 --> 15:37.707
everyone turned their heads
at once,

15:37.707 --> 15:40.964
like, as if they heard a sound,
but I didn't hear anything.

15:50.232 --> 15:52.571
‐ Two people,
a‐a man and a woman,

15:52.571 --> 15:55.577
they just‐‐they started
shooting people.

15:55.577 --> 15:59.626
All the ones that didn't
walk off after the statue.

15:59.626 --> 16:01.630
‐ And then we found each other.

16:01.630 --> 16:05.597
‐ Who?
‐ Evelyn and Ingalls...

16:05.597 --> 16:07.684
the nurse.

16:07.684 --> 16:09.938
‐ Did you hear
that fucking sound?

16:09.938 --> 16:12.067
<i>ANNIE: No.</i>

16:12.067 --> 16:14.071
My girl...

16:16.075 --> 16:18.831
Joy‐‐she did.

16:18.831 --> 16:21.419
<i>And she fell in line.</i>

16:23.591 --> 16:26.387
So, like I said, can I‐‐
‐ Hold on.

16:26.387 --> 16:28.601
‐ What, you don't trust me?

16:28.601 --> 16:31.649
How about I don't trust you?

16:31.649 --> 16:35.113
All of this is down
to your blood!

16:35.113 --> 16:37.786
Your cock‐a‐doodie nephew!

16:37.786 --> 16:40.708
I did kill him.

16:40.708 --> 16:44.800
‐ What?
‐ Just like you thought.

16:44.800 --> 16:49.267
And I dumped him
in the wrong dang place.

16:49.267 --> 16:52.439
The wrongest place.
‐ Where?

16:52.439 --> 16:54.820
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:54.820 --> 16:57.366
‐ That construction site.
‐ Near Marsten?

16:57.366 --> 16:59.997
‐ It's what's‐‐
what's underneath.

16:59.997 --> 17:01.625
‐ What's underneath?

17:01.625 --> 17:02.669
‐ Tunnels!

17:02.669 --> 17:05.048
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:05.048 --> 17:06.342
‐ Draw it.

17:06.342 --> 17:13.356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:14.818 --> 17:17.197
ANNIE: At first, I thought
it was just my brain

17:17.197 --> 17:21.372
shorting out on me,
but it was real!

17:21.372 --> 17:28.345
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:29.556 --> 17:31.977
‐ You think she's one of them?

17:31.977 --> 17:34.858
‐ I think she's bipolar,
for starters.

17:34.858 --> 17:37.822
But, no, I don't.

17:37.822 --> 17:42.624
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:42.624 --> 17:44.586
‐ What happened
to your earring?

17:44.586 --> 17:48.761
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:48.761 --> 17:51.307
Come on, J, you hooked me up
to chemo how many times?

17:51.307 --> 17:53.771
We're practically coworkers.

17:53.771 --> 17:56.652
You had a diamond stud
in your ear three days ago.

17:56.652 --> 17:58.823
Today...

17:58.823 --> 18:02.079
there's not even a dent
in your earlobe.

18:02.079 --> 18:03.791
[coughing]

18:03.791 --> 18:06.964
It's all...
[coughing]

18:06.964 --> 18:08.634
Healed up.

18:08.634 --> 18:13.143
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:13.143 --> 18:14.813
What I'm trying to figure out

18:14.813 --> 18:16.482
is why they'd sneak you
in here.

18:16.482 --> 18:18.445
Why didn't they just
storm the place?

18:18.445 --> 18:20.449
[coughs]

18:20.449 --> 18:25.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:25.542 --> 18:27.630
[clattering]

18:27.630 --> 18:31.179
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:31.179 --> 18:35.145
[gunshot]
‐ [shouting]

18:35.145 --> 18:38.569
[groaning]

18:48.839 --> 18:50.467
‐ And this drug,
Haldol‐‐

18:50.467 --> 18:52.304
you're saying
it flips them back?

18:52.304 --> 18:55.018
‐ Yeah, but only for a time.
I saw it work on Chris.

18:56.897 --> 19:00.070
<i>He became himself again</i>
<i>after every injection...</i>

19:00.070 --> 19:01.990
[indistinct chatter]

19:01.990 --> 19:03.828
<i>Until it wore off.</i>

19:03.828 --> 19:06.583
ABDI: How much drug do we have?
NADIA: Enough.

19:06.583 --> 19:08.253
I think if we
give him the full four mil,

19:08.253 --> 19:09.673
we'll talk to the Jamal
we know.

19:09.673 --> 19:11.384
ABDI: Then what?

19:11.384 --> 19:13.346
POP: Then he tells us how we
can stop them‐‐

19:13.346 --> 19:17.564
their weaknesses,
how we fucking kill them?

19:17.564 --> 19:20.193
‐ They still have the memories
of the other one.

19:20.193 --> 19:21.529
Chris did.

19:21.529 --> 19:22.991
‐ Prisoner in your own body?

19:24.493 --> 19:26.247
‐ He's awake.

19:26.247 --> 19:28.459
‐ You tried to kill him.
Why?

19:28.459 --> 19:31.382
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:31.382 --> 19:33.011
Jamal will tell us.
He knows what you know.

19:33.011 --> 19:35.473
JAMAL: [laughing]

19:35.473 --> 19:37.394
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.394 --> 19:39.440
Let him, then.

19:39.440 --> 19:41.319
It's over.

19:41.319 --> 19:43.197
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:43.197 --> 19:46.454
Tomorrow at dusk,
she returns.

19:48.041 --> 19:51.047
‐ He's a friend.
I don't understand
how‐‐how someone could just‐‐

19:51.047 --> 19:55.890
‐ It's not his fault.
It's not even him.

19:55.890 --> 19:58.896
‐ Okay, well, I just‐‐
I don't understand any of this.

19:58.896 --> 20:00.190
[gun clicking]

20:00.190 --> 20:02.654
[fluttering]

20:04.323 --> 20:07.789
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:07.789 --> 20:14.761
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:14.761 --> 20:17.558
‐ 400 years
she's been gathering speed,

20:17.558 --> 20:19.103
heading for this place
at this time,

20:19.103 --> 20:20.438
and you think you can stop her?

20:20.438 --> 20:21.984
‐ You know what I think?

20:21.984 --> 20:23.821
I think there's a reason
your boss sent

20:23.821 --> 20:26.242
an assassin to kill me instead
of breaking down the door.

20:26.242 --> 20:29.248
[clattering]

20:29.248 --> 20:35.218
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:35.218 --> 20:37.890
[vehicle engine rumbling]

20:37.890 --> 20:40.437
‐ Oh. Oh, Jesus.
[car door closes]

20:40.437 --> 20:42.315
POP: I think you
need something.

20:42.315 --> 20:44.111
That's what I think.

20:44.111 --> 20:46.157
Something that only I have.

20:46.157 --> 20:47.451
Huh?

20:47.451 --> 20:50.540
[clattering]

20:50.540 --> 20:57.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:03.107 --> 21:04.234
[fluttering]

21:04.234 --> 21:05.905
‐ He's here.

21:05.905 --> 21:07.074
<i>PERSON ON RADIO:</i>
<i>Pop.</i>

21:07.074 --> 21:10.080
[clattering]

21:10.080 --> 21:11.958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:11.958 --> 21:15.507
<i>Pop Merrill,</i>
<i>come back.</i>

21:15.507 --> 21:22.521
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:29.243 --> 21:30.830
<i>Come back, Pop.</i>

21:30.830 --> 21:37.802
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.475 --> 21:43.479
<i>Let's make a deal.</i>

21:43.479 --> 21:47.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:47.237 --> 21:50.243
[buzzing and fluttering]

21:50.243 --> 21:57.257
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:04.354 --> 22:08.446
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:08.446 --> 22:12.997
‐ So you want to discuss
the terms of your surrender?

22:12.997 --> 22:15.586
You caught me at a good time.
Shoot.

22:15.586 --> 22:17.798
<i>PERSON ON RADIO: Uh...</i>
‐ Oh, Jesus.

22:17.798 --> 22:19.677
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:19.677 --> 22:21.013
Oh, God.
‐ Shh!

22:21.013 --> 22:23.727
‐ Delusions...

22:23.727 --> 22:27.442
normal for a man
in your advanced age.

22:27.442 --> 22:30.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:30.281 --> 22:31.993
POP:
Whoever you are,

22:31.993 --> 22:34.373
I'm guessing your age is a lot
more advanced than mine.

22:34.373 --> 22:36.418
<i>AUGUSTIN:</i>
<i>You're smarter than I thought.</i>

22:36.418 --> 22:38.381
We've got a lot to talk about.

22:38.381 --> 22:40.134
POP: We sure do.

22:40.134 --> 22:42.264
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:42.264 --> 22:45.061
What do I call you, new guy?

22:45.061 --> 22:47.065
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:47.065 --> 22:49.444
‐ My name is Augustin.

22:49.444 --> 22:51.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:51.407 --> 22:53.077
<i>POP: Well, Augustin,</i>

22:53.077 --> 22:56.166
I've been catching up
on some old correspondence

22:56.166 --> 22:58.254
from Dale Lacy.

22:58.254 --> 22:59.423
Remember him?

22:59.423 --> 23:01.260
<i>That's why you're here, right?</i>

23:01.260 --> 23:03.306
<i>You need to know what he knew.</i>

23:03.306 --> 23:10.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:10.320 --> 23:12.490
‐ So you want to hear my offer?

23:12.490 --> 23:16.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:16.206 --> 23:18.670
<i>You give me</i>
<i>the warden's letters,</i>

23:18.670 --> 23:20.591
I'll let Nadia and Abdi go,

23:20.591 --> 23:22.762
<i>along with whoever else</i>
<i>you've got in there.</i>

23:22.762 --> 23:25.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:25.391 --> 23:27.980
<i>Or...</i>

23:27.980 --> 23:31.487
we could do this another way.

23:31.487 --> 23:36.330
<i>Decided how many people</i>
<i>you want to see die tonight?</i>

23:36.330 --> 23:37.958
‐ We're not the ones
who'll be dying.

23:37.958 --> 23:40.798
I got bombs on every door
and window.

23:43.970 --> 23:46.183
NADIA:
We have 55 minutes.

23:46.183 --> 23:48.020
It's the only way out.
<i>AUGUSTIN: Pop...</i>

23:48.020 --> 23:49.481
Just need extra time.

23:49.481 --> 23:51.569
<i>AUGUSTIN: Let's make a deal.</i>
‐ Really?

23:51.569 --> 23:53.280
<i>You're gonna let them go?</i>

23:53.280 --> 23:55.493
Why? You're killing everyone
else left in Castle Rock?

23:55.493 --> 24:00.211
[coughing]

24:00.211 --> 24:01.338
<i>AUGUSTIN: Pop.</i>

24:03.927 --> 24:06.766
<i>Pop Merrill,</i>
<i>come back.</i>

24:06.766 --> 24:08.770
[gun clicks]

24:13.738 --> 24:15.450
‐ Okay, so we're
fucking surrounded.

24:15.450 --> 24:17.036
‐ Yeah, we have a plan.

24:17.036 --> 24:18.289
CHANCE:
Okay.

24:18.289 --> 24:19.541
NADIA:
We need to find a way out

24:19.541 --> 24:21.378
before they find a way in.

24:21.378 --> 24:23.633
CHANCE: And how are we supposed
to do that?

24:23.633 --> 24:25.011
NADIA: The train.

24:25.011 --> 24:26.639
‐ It's gonna be
the Maine/Boston.

24:26.639 --> 24:28.727
‐ That train's a mile long
and always on time.

24:28.727 --> 24:30.480
‐ We're gonna jump on
to a train?

24:30.480 --> 24:32.484
‐ In front of a train.
‐ Oh, okay.

24:32.484 --> 24:34.112
NADIA: It was a game
we played as kids.

24:34.112 --> 24:35.406
ABDI:
Hurry! Before he sees us!

24:35.406 --> 24:36.951
Come on!
‐ Hurry up! He's coming!

24:36.951 --> 24:39.456
[train horn blares]
ABDI: Come on, Nadia!

24:39.456 --> 24:41.126
PERSON: Go, go, go, go!
ABDI: Nadia, hurry!

24:41.126 --> 24:43.506
Mostly to get away from Ace.

24:43.506 --> 24:45.636
POP: How's that for a fucking
cosmic joke?

24:45.636 --> 24:47.263
‐ It cuts the town in half.

24:47.263 --> 24:49.059
<i>You can't get across</i>
<i>for half an hour.</i>

24:49.059 --> 24:50.938
We get on the other side,
they won't catch us.

24:50.938 --> 24:53.652
‐ I don't know
if I can make it, Nad.

24:53.652 --> 24:55.279
‐ No man left behind, right?

24:55.279 --> 24:57.408
[electricity whirring]

24:57.408 --> 24:58.620
Generator, fuck.

24:58.620 --> 24:59.956
‐ I'm on it.
‐ No, I'll do it.

24:59.956 --> 25:01.250
‐ You shouldn't go alone.

25:01.250 --> 25:08.222
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:11.771 --> 25:13.232
NADIA:
Keep up.

25:16.029 --> 25:18.618
It's just down here.

25:18.618 --> 25:24.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:26.008 --> 25:30.099
[buzzing, fluttering]
‐ [grunts]

25:30.099 --> 25:35.861
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:37.740 --> 25:39.409
Where's Anne?

25:39.409 --> 25:41.873
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:41.873 --> 25:45.046
‐ I need to know where they've
got my daughter in that house‐‐

25:45.046 --> 25:46.799
what room, et cetera,

25:46.799 --> 25:49.179
and any other little details
you can help me out with.

25:49.179 --> 25:51.475
‐ And why would I ever tell you
any of that?

25:51.475 --> 25:53.688
‐ [sighs]

25:53.688 --> 25:55.483
Maybe you wouldn't.

26:06.088 --> 26:08.092
But I have put down quite
a few of your brothers

26:08.092 --> 26:09.469
and sisters tonight,

26:09.469 --> 26:11.264
so maybe that carries
some weight.

26:18.237 --> 26:20.784
You folks have some experience
with pain.

26:23.288 --> 26:25.042
Is that right?

26:25.042 --> 26:27.673
<i>WHISPERING VOICE:</i>
<i>Annie...</i>

26:27.673 --> 26:30.637
<i>find her.</i>

26:30.637 --> 26:32.098
‐ So do I.

26:33.601 --> 26:35.521
What I can't get
my kadooza around

26:35.521 --> 26:39.154
is why they're keeping
you alive.

26:39.154 --> 26:41.450
Maybe they're still living in
a world where reasonable people

26:41.450 --> 26:42.703
can come to an arrangement.

26:42.703 --> 26:44.080
I would love that.

26:44.080 --> 26:47.086
I'm as reasonable as they come.

26:47.086 --> 26:48.130
But...

26:49.884 --> 26:51.763
I have spent some time
in that house of yours.

26:51.763 --> 26:53.348
And sorry.

26:53.348 --> 26:59.945
You folks don't seem
very reasonable at all.

26:59.945 --> 27:02.951
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:02.951 --> 27:06.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:06.541 --> 27:08.630
‐ Do you really think
she's better off with you?

27:08.630 --> 27:14.975
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:14.975 --> 27:18.232
You see, I knew what he knew‐‐
Jamal‐‐

27:18.232 --> 27:20.194
and I remember the hallway.

27:20.194 --> 27:21.697
<i>[Annie crying]</i>

27:21.697 --> 27:23.450
JAMAL: Anne?

27:23.450 --> 27:25.204
What are you doing?

27:25.204 --> 27:28.126
Even if you find her,
after what we've done to her,

27:28.126 --> 27:29.630
she'll never be the same.

27:29.630 --> 27:31.174
<i>WHISPERING VOICE:</i>
<i>A good mother</i>

27:31.174 --> 27:32.636
<i>would never let this happen.</i>

27:32.636 --> 27:34.807
‐ You'll look into those eyes,

27:34.807 --> 27:37.436
and you won't know
who's looking back.

27:40.401 --> 27:43.950
[screaming]

27:43.950 --> 27:47.874
‐ [breathing heavily]

27:54.888 --> 27:56.934
‐ [gasps]
You killed him!

27:56.934 --> 27:58.437
He was meant to help us!

27:58.437 --> 28:00.775
Do you never think, Anne?

28:00.775 --> 28:04.032
<i>[tense music]</i>

28:04.032 --> 28:11.046
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:11.046 --> 28:12.883
[no audio]

28:12.883 --> 28:19.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:41.649 --> 28:44.655
<i>[I Am Kloot's</i>
<i>"Avenue of Hope"]</i>

28:44.655 --> 28:51.669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:11.207 --> 29:15.132
SINGER:
♪ Along the avenue of hope ♪

29:15.132 --> 29:17.971
♪ The footsteps falter ♪

29:17.971 --> 29:21.060
♪ The fingers grope ♪

29:21.060 --> 29:23.356
♪ And the days ♪

29:23.356 --> 29:27.824
♪ Stretch out
beneath the sun ♪

29:27.824 --> 29:30.705
♪ ♪

29:30.705 --> 29:34.713
♪ No one's born,
no one dies ♪

29:34.713 --> 29:36.257
‐ Pop.

29:36.257 --> 29:40.934
SINGER: ♪ No one loves,
so no one cries ♪

29:40.934 --> 29:46.904
♪ And we wait to see just what
we will become ♪

29:46.904 --> 29:48.532
<i>AUGUSTIN:</i>
<i>Pop...</i>

29:48.532 --> 29:50.494
[Pop coughs]

29:50.494 --> 29:52.958
SINGER:
♪ Don't let me falter ♪

29:52.958 --> 29:55.254
♪ Don't let me ride ♪

29:55.254 --> 29:59.888
♪ Don't let the earth
in me subside ♪

29:59.888 --> 30:01.892
♪ ♪

30:01.892 --> 30:07.319
♪ Let me see just who
I will become ♪

30:07.319 --> 30:09.323
‐ [groaning]

30:09.323 --> 30:13.833
♪ ♪

30:13.833 --> 30:16.296
I thought we'd be killing
each other by now,

30:16.296 --> 30:18.341
like civilized human beings.

30:20.470 --> 30:23.644
‐ Well, I know how much
you love a deal.

30:25.188 --> 30:27.569
I thought I'd try you
one last time.

30:29.990 --> 30:33.163
Your bombs will slow us down.

30:33.163 --> 30:36.795
<i>They'll slow us down,</i>
<i>but they won't stop us.</i>

30:36.795 --> 30:40.135
<i>I prefer a softer landing,</i>
<i>though.</i>

30:41.512 --> 30:43.350
<i>I bet you do, too.</i>

30:44.895 --> 30:48.736
‐ No, I don't do deals
with walking fucking corpses.

30:48.736 --> 30:52.076
‐ Which is funny,
coming from a walking corpse.

30:54.915 --> 30:58.171
‐ You know the difference
between me and you, Gus?

30:58.171 --> 31:01.762
You're a hitchhiker
in borrowed clothing,

31:01.762 --> 31:04.266
and I know who I fucking am.

31:04.266 --> 31:07.231
‐ [laughs]
Pop...

31:07.231 --> 31:08.818
[laughs]

31:08.818 --> 31:11.615
You don't at all.

31:11.615 --> 31:14.286
<i>That's why you're always</i>
<i>looking for a trade.</i>

31:15.623 --> 31:18.003
<i>You are remarkably empty</i>
<i>of purpose...</i>

31:19.463 --> 31:21.342
<i>Of destiny.</i>

31:21.342 --> 31:23.096
That's why your life
is gonna end here

31:23.096 --> 31:25.183
in this tower of garbage,

31:25.183 --> 31:28.314
<i>this castle of shit.</i>

31:28.314 --> 31:29.818
[clocks ticking]

31:29.818 --> 31:32.824
<i>All these little...</i>

31:32.824 --> 31:35.203
<i>insignificant trades</i>

31:35.203 --> 31:38.711
<i>adding up to a tomb of trash.</i>

31:38.711 --> 31:41.215
See, I know everything he knew.

31:43.846 --> 31:45.767
‐ Who?
‐ Your nephew.

31:45.767 --> 31:48.313
<i>POP: Then you're</i>
<i>a fucking moron.</i>

31:48.313 --> 31:51.862
‐ I remember what he felt.
You know what he felt for you?

31:51.862 --> 31:55.578
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:55.578 --> 31:56.830
Love.

31:56.830 --> 31:59.418
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:59.418 --> 32:01.506
‐ [coughs]
<i>AUGUSTIN: To think,</i>

32:01.506 --> 32:03.552
<i>underneath it all,</i>

32:03.552 --> 32:06.809
<i>that angry little boy...</i>

32:06.809 --> 32:08.520
<i>he loved you.</i>

32:08.520 --> 32:10.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:10.232 --> 32:11.985
<i>You.</i>

32:11.985 --> 32:14.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:14.323 --> 32:16.244
<i>But...</i>

32:16.244 --> 32:19.291
<i>you hit him...</i>

32:19.291 --> 32:21.504
<i>a lot...</i>

32:21.504 --> 32:23.926
<i>when he was small.</i>

32:23.926 --> 32:26.097
A lot.

32:26.097 --> 32:29.896
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:29.896 --> 32:32.610
<i>POP:</i>
<i>Well, he was bad a lot.</i>

32:32.610 --> 32:36.910
From the jump,
like his dad.

32:36.910 --> 32:40.208
In my house,
you pay your debts.

32:40.208 --> 32:42.087
He knew the rules.

32:42.087 --> 32:43.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:43.841 --> 32:45.343
‐ It's extraordinary.

32:45.343 --> 32:47.472
No children of your own,

32:47.472 --> 32:49.476
but ruined four kids anyway.

32:49.476 --> 32:51.272
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:51.272 --> 32:53.276
<i>To start with nothing</i>

32:53.276 --> 32:56.032
<i>and somehow end up</i>
<i>with less than nothing...</i>

32:56.032 --> 32:57.952
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:57.952 --> 32:59.956
<i>That takes a real businessman.</i>

32:59.956 --> 33:06.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:15.028 --> 33:16.990
<i>POP: I've been trying</i>
<i>to understand</i>

33:16.990 --> 33:20.413
<i>what could be so important</i>
<i>in these here letters.</i>

33:20.413 --> 33:22.752
And I don't know much
about your kind,

33:22.752 --> 33:24.631
but I think I can guess.

33:24.631 --> 33:26.927
<i>The way I figure,</i>
<i>you're trying to understand</i>

33:26.927 --> 33:30.726
<i>who the fuck Lacy had in that</i>
<i>cage and where he is now.</i>

33:30.726 --> 33:32.730
Well, you're not
gonna find out,

33:32.730 --> 33:35.443
<i>'cause I burned</i>
<i>your fucking letters.</i>

33:35.443 --> 33:42.457
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:56.402 --> 33:58.489
‐ I don't care about
the letters, Pop.

33:58.489 --> 33:59.868
<i>I have you.</i>

33:59.868 --> 34:04.669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:04.669 --> 34:08.134
<i>You read them,</i>
<i>so I'll take you instead.</i>

34:08.134 --> 34:10.013
<i>I'll make you one of us, Pop,</i>

34:10.013 --> 34:12.309
<i>and you'll tell me everything.</i>

34:12.309 --> 34:15.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:15.900 --> 34:16.902
Pop.

34:16.902 --> 34:22.872
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:22.872 --> 34:24.375
<i>Pop.</i>

34:24.375 --> 34:27.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:27.799 --> 34:30.011
ABDI: Don't let him get
into your head.

34:30.011 --> 34:33.644
‐ [coughs]

34:33.644 --> 34:36.608
That part about...

34:36.608 --> 34:39.071
me fucking up
all four of you...

34:40.950 --> 34:45.250
‐ Pop, it's‐‐it's too late
for this shit.

34:45.250 --> 34:47.880
‐ Be honest.

34:49.174 --> 34:51.805
‐ [sighs]
Yeah.

34:51.805 --> 34:53.391
‐ Yeah, what?

34:55.646 --> 34:58.276
‐ Yeah, you fucked us up.

34:58.276 --> 35:00.698
I mean,
you want me to lie?

35:00.698 --> 35:02.451
‐ I fed you.

35:02.451 --> 35:04.706
I protected you.

35:04.706 --> 35:07.002
I taught you.

35:07.002 --> 35:08.421
Even when my life was shit,

35:08.421 --> 35:10.843
I tried to make
your life better.

35:10.843 --> 35:14.433
Even when I didn't
feel like it.

35:14.433 --> 35:19.234
And you should know,
I really fucking felt like it.

35:20.696 --> 35:23.660
And here you are.

35:23.660 --> 35:25.998
‐ Here I am.

35:25.998 --> 35:27.459
Here we are.

35:27.459 --> 35:29.756
Here's what you
always wanted to hear

35:29.756 --> 35:31.676
from my ungrateful mouth.

35:31.676 --> 35:34.431
Thank you for liberating me.

35:37.312 --> 35:38.982
Look at me.

35:38.982 --> 35:41.070
I'm liberated.

36:03.114 --> 36:05.118
‐ They still fit?

36:05.118 --> 36:07.038
‐ Yeah.

36:12.465 --> 36:14.261
‐ He'll come soon.

36:15.890 --> 36:19.479
He's patient,
but not that patient.

36:21.191 --> 36:25.910
[clears throat, coughing]

36:25.910 --> 36:27.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:27.955 --> 36:29.918
[coughing]

36:29.918 --> 36:31.630
[breathes deeply]

36:31.630 --> 36:33.550
‐ Breathe.
POP: Huh?

36:33.550 --> 36:35.888
[coughing]

36:35.888 --> 36:39.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:39.102 --> 36:43.527
When that fucking train comes,
I'm gonna slow you down, Nadia.

36:43.527 --> 36:45.365
‐ It's just a few yards
across the track.

36:45.365 --> 36:46.826
Once we're past‐‐

36:46.826 --> 36:48.747
‐ Well, if I don't make it
out of this,

36:48.747 --> 36:51.043
things I want to say.
‐ Stop.

36:51.043 --> 36:54.508
‐ I want to tell you that...

36:54.508 --> 36:58.767
seeing all those graduations
meant to me...

36:58.767 --> 37:00.646
All you've done,
all you've accomplished‐‐

37:00.646 --> 37:02.065
‐ Stop it.

37:02.065 --> 37:03.652
‐ No, I just‐‐I want‐‐
I want to say it.

37:03.652 --> 37:05.196
NADIA: But I don't
want to hear it.

37:05.196 --> 37:07.910
There's not gonna be a time
after this, okay?

37:07.910 --> 37:09.454
Not for us.

37:09.454 --> 37:11.542
‐ I know you're gonna be mad
at me forever.

37:11.542 --> 37:13.045
I‐I get that.

37:13.045 --> 37:15.592
NADIA: You don't get
to make your peace.

37:15.592 --> 37:18.222
That's what I'm trying
to tell you,

37:18.222 --> 37:21.646
and I'm not gonna be mad
at you forever.

37:21.646 --> 37:24.151
If I live through this night,

37:24.151 --> 37:27.198
I'm gonna leave this place.

37:27.198 --> 37:29.787
And I'm never gonna think
of you again.

37:29.787 --> 37:32.542
[footsteps approaching]

37:35.298 --> 37:38.137
‐ We good here?

37:38.137 --> 37:40.349
‐ Good as we're gonna be.

38:00.098 --> 38:03.104
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:03.104 --> 38:10.118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:42.892 --> 38:46.023
‐ Pop,
we'll give you a quiet end,

38:46.023 --> 38:47.483
<i>entombed in one of us.</i>

38:47.483 --> 38:49.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:49.572 --> 38:54.289
You can subside...gracefully,

38:54.289 --> 38:56.794
knowing that you did
one good thing

38:56.794 --> 38:59.049
<i>in your gaping vacancy</i>
<i>of a life.</i>

38:59.049 --> 39:04.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:04.267 --> 39:05.646
‐ I don't know.

39:05.646 --> 39:07.900
Nobody really retires
these days.

39:07.900 --> 39:12.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:12.075 --> 39:16.751
<i>I got myself in a vest here,</i>
<i>loaded up with C4.</i>

39:16.751 --> 39:19.297
‐ Pop‐‐
<i>POP: I'm guessing</i>
<i>that when it blows,</i>

39:19.297 --> 39:22.303
<i>it ain't gonna be so easy</i>
<i>to bring me back.</i>

39:26.353 --> 39:30.904
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:30.904 --> 39:33.910
[shouting in French]

39:33.910 --> 39:40.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:00.839 --> 40:02.634
[car engine revving]

40:09.272 --> 40:12.320
[people shouting in French]

40:12.320 --> 40:15.952
[explosion, glass shattering]

40:22.966 --> 40:24.762
‐ Looks like we're leaving
earlier than we thought.

40:24.762 --> 40:26.473
Down to the back staircase
through the cellar.

40:26.473 --> 40:27.810
Abdi, stay with me.
NADIA: Let's go!

40:27.810 --> 40:30.147
POP: Go, go, go, go, go!
NADIA: Move!

40:30.147 --> 40:33.738
[indistinct shouting]

40:33.738 --> 40:36.744
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:36.744 --> 40:38.748
‐ [speaking French]

40:38.748 --> 40:41.461
[engine turning over]

40:41.461 --> 40:43.633
[shouting continues]

40:43.633 --> 40:46.346
[tires squealing]

40:46.346 --> 40:52.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:54.320 --> 40:57.160
[glass shatters]

40:57.160 --> 41:00.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:00.625 --> 41:02.754
ABDI:
Here, take this one, too.

41:02.754 --> 41:06.554
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:06.554 --> 41:09.560
[shouting continues]

41:09.560 --> 41:16.574
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:25.800 --> 41:28.973
[objects clatter]

41:28.973 --> 41:31.979
[indistinct chatter outside]

41:38.283 --> 41:44.128
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:46.508 --> 41:47.719
‐ [breathing heavily]

41:47.719 --> 41:50.432
‐ Hello, Georgia.
Freak time.

41:50.432 --> 41:51.769
[gunshot]
‐ [grunts]

41:51.769 --> 41:53.898
[coughs]

41:53.898 --> 41:56.528
[breathing heavily]

41:56.528 --> 42:03.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:19.240 --> 42:22.706
[gun cocks]
‐ [breathing heavily]

42:22.706 --> 42:29.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:40.491 --> 42:42.453
ANNIE:
You guys okay?

42:42.453 --> 42:44.290
How many of them behind you?
‐ We don't know.

42:44.290 --> 42:46.503
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:46.503 --> 42:48.006
[explosion]

42:48.006 --> 42:49.425
‐ Go, go, go!
NADIA: Come on, let's go.

42:49.425 --> 42:51.012
[guns cocking]
Go, go, go!

42:51.012 --> 42:56.272
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:56.272 --> 42:57.734
‐ Hey.

42:57.734 --> 43:01.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:03.495 --> 43:05.750
‐ Go, go, go, go!

43:05.750 --> 43:08.213
ABDI:
Pop, come on! Pop!

43:08.213 --> 43:09.967
‐ You need more time.

43:09.967 --> 43:11.428
‐ Pop!

43:11.428 --> 43:18.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:21.866 --> 43:23.285
‐ [spits]

43:23.285 --> 43:30.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:31.468 --> 43:33.013
‐ Where's Pop?

43:33.013 --> 43:40.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:49.546 --> 43:50.882
[gunshot]

43:50.882 --> 43:52.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:52.176 --> 43:53.386
[gunshots]
‐ [screams]

43:53.386 --> 43:55.390
[gun cocking]

44:08.166 --> 44:09.711
[gun cocks]

44:09.711 --> 44:13.176
[gunshot]

44:13.176 --> 44:16.851
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:16.851 --> 44:18.478
[gunshot]

44:18.478 --> 44:25.492
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:40.314 --> 44:41.650
‐ Keep going.

44:41.650 --> 44:46.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:46.702 --> 44:48.748
[gunshot]

44:48.748 --> 44:55.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:04.988 --> 45:08.370
[gas hissing]

45:08.370 --> 45:11.459
‐ [screaming]

45:16.887 --> 45:19.893
[hissing continues]

45:19.893 --> 45:26.907
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:26.907 --> 45:29.913
[fire crackling]

46:09.868 --> 46:12.874
[train horn blowing
in the distance]

46:12.874 --> 46:14.795
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:14.795 --> 46:16.965
EVELYN: The train!
We have to go!

46:16.965 --> 46:18.510
‐ Wait.

46:18.510 --> 46:20.472
‐ Evelyn!

46:20.472 --> 46:27.486
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:31.829 --> 46:33.833
[door creaks closed]

46:33.833 --> 46:35.293
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:35.293 --> 46:37.549
[gunshots]

46:42.266 --> 46:43.811
‐ [gasping]

46:43.811 --> 46:45.815
[static whirring]

46:45.815 --> 46:52.829
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:57.421 --> 47:00.260
‐ Careful, now.

47:00.260 --> 47:02.472
Careful, careful, careful.

47:02.472 --> 47:04.101
[gunshot]

47:10.573 --> 47:12.451
‐ [screams]

47:12.451 --> 47:15.791
‐ How deep you got
the bodies stacked, Gus?

47:15.791 --> 47:17.795
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:17.795 --> 47:20.885
Do you slip into a new one
like a kimono?

47:20.885 --> 47:23.682
Or is it
a little more complicated?

47:23.682 --> 47:25.686
‐ [gasps]

47:25.686 --> 47:28.358
‐ Ah...

47:28.358 --> 47:32.157
So you can't just spoon up
whatever dog food's left

47:32.157 --> 47:34.370
into your fancy magic coffin.

47:34.370 --> 47:36.290
This goes up,

47:36.290 --> 47:38.796
the whole place
goes up with us.

47:38.796 --> 47:40.549
Looks like you're not
gonna be around

47:40.549 --> 47:42.720
to see your brave old world.

47:42.720 --> 47:45.601
‐ Pop.
Reginald.

47:48.983 --> 47:50.987
Don't.
‐ Why not?

47:50.987 --> 47:54.285
You just spent the last hour
telling me I'm a piece of shit.

47:54.285 --> 47:56.289
Now you're gonna tell me what?

47:56.289 --> 47:59.671
That my life is suddenly
worth something?

47:59.671 --> 48:02.092
That I'm a good man?

48:02.092 --> 48:05.098
[train horn blowing
in the distance]

48:07.227 --> 48:08.856
‐ No.

48:08.856 --> 48:11.611
You're not a good man.

48:11.611 --> 48:13.031
You're a dying one.

48:13.031 --> 48:14.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:14.909 --> 48:18.416
[gunshots]

48:18.416 --> 48:21.380
‐ Anne, shoot!

48:23.927 --> 48:25.472
‐ [screams]

48:25.472 --> 48:32.486
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:35.325 --> 48:37.997
‐ And I am a deathless one.

48:37.997 --> 48:40.377
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:40.377 --> 48:44.844
You have nothing.
I have forever.

48:44.844 --> 48:48.852
Don't tell me you're not
interested in a trade.

48:48.852 --> 48:51.566
Don't tell me you don't want
what I've got.

48:51.566 --> 48:58.580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:00.250 --> 49:02.379
‐ Hmm, no deal.
‐ No!

49:02.379 --> 49:06.680
[train horn blowing
in the distance]

49:06.680 --> 49:09.686
[breathing shakily]

49:11.731 --> 49:13.861
‐ [grunts]

49:13.861 --> 49:17.159
[laughing]

49:17.159 --> 49:20.165
<i>[Laura Marling's</i>
<i>"What He Wrote"]</i>

49:20.165 --> 49:23.589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:23.589 --> 49:25.801
‐ Come on!
[train horn blowing]

49:25.801 --> 49:31.103
MARLING: ♪ Forgive me here,
I cannot stay ♪

49:31.103 --> 49:33.524
[indistinct shouting]
♪ He cut off my tongue ♪

49:33.524 --> 49:37.157
♪ There is nothing to say ♪

49:37.157 --> 49:38.911
[Pop coughing]

49:38.911 --> 49:40.915
MARLING:
♪ Love me, oh, Lord ♪

49:40.915 --> 49:42.919
♪ He threw me away ♪

49:42.919 --> 49:48.722
♪ He laughed at my sins,
in his arms I must stay ♪

49:48.722 --> 49:50.851
[indistinct shouting]

49:50.851 --> 49:52.939
[train horn blowing]

49:52.939 --> 49:55.527
MARLING:
♪ That gave you your name ♪

49:55.527 --> 49:57.322
♪ He had to leave ♪

49:57.322 --> 50:01.080
♪ Though I begged him
to stay ♪

50:01.080 --> 50:02.750
[train horn blowing]

50:02.750 --> 50:06.257
MARLING: ♪ Left me alone
when I needed the light ♪

50:06.257 --> 50:11.560
♪ Fell to my knees,
and I wept for my life ♪

50:11.560 --> 50:15.776
♪ If he had have stayed,
you might understand ♪

50:15.776 --> 50:17.112
‐ You'll see.

50:17.112 --> 50:18.740
MARLING:
♪ If he had have stayed ♪

50:18.740 --> 50:21.537
♪ You never would have taken
my hand ♪

50:21.537 --> 50:24.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:24.042 --> 50:27.424
♪ He wrote I'm‐‐ ♪

50:27.424 --> 50:29.679
[music stops]

50:35.566 --> 50:37.527
‐ Pop!

50:37.527 --> 50:39.574
Come in, Pop!

50:39.574 --> 50:40.826
<i>Pop!</i>

50:40.826 --> 50:42.872
<i>[train rumbling]</i>

50:42.872 --> 50:44.166
<i>Pop, come in!</i>

50:44.166 --> 50:46.546
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:46.546 --> 50:49.886
MARLING: ♪ Begged him to stay
in my cold wooden grip ♪

50:49.886 --> 50:52.515
‐ Pop!
Pop, do you copy, Pop?

50:52.515 --> 50:56.065
MARLING: ♪ Begged him to stay
by the light of this ship ♪

50:56.065 --> 50:57.484
♪ Me fighting him ♪

50:57.484 --> 50:59.112
‐ Pop?

50:59.112 --> 51:00.991
WOMAN: ♪ Fighting light
fighting dawn ♪

51:00.991 --> 51:02.870
♪ And the waves came
and stole him ♪

51:02.870 --> 51:05.333
‐ Pop?
Do you copy, Pop?

51:05.333 --> 51:07.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:07.630 --> 51:10.009
MARLING:
♪ We write ♪

51:10.009 --> 51:12.640
♪ That's all right ♪

51:12.640 --> 51:15.395
♪ I miss his smell ♪

51:15.395 --> 51:18.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>
